Make flax eggs: Whisk @flaxseed meal{14%g} with @warm water{90%ml} in a small bowl. Let sit until thick and gel-like, about ~{10%minutes}. This replaces the whole egg + 2 yolks.

Whisk dry ingredients: Whisk together @all-purpose flour{330%g}, @bread flour{30%g}, @baking soda{5%g}, @baking powder{3%g}, @cornstarch{5%g}, @fine sea salt{3%g}, and @ground cinnamon{2%g}.

Cream butter and sugars: With paddle attachment on medium speed, cream @Earth Balance Vegan Buttery Sticks{240%g} (softened, 65-68°F), @granulated sugar{190%g}, and @light brown sugar{230%g} until light and fluffy, about ~{2%minutes}.

Add wet ingredients: On low speed, add the prepared flax egg mixture, then @vanilla extract{10%g}. Mix about ~{1%minute} until smooth. The mixture may look slightly broken — that's fine.

Combine: On low speed, add the dry ingredients until just incorporated. Do not overmix.

Fold in chocolate: Mix in @dairy-free chocolate chips{340%g} briefly until evenly distributed. Do not overmix.

Prep pans: Line a half sheet and two quarter sheets with parchment.

Scoop dough: Portion @dough{about 50%g} balls, well-spaced apart (6 per quarter sheet).

Wrap: Tightly wrap dough balls with plastic wrap to prevent drying out.

Chill dough: Refrigerate wrapped dough for ~{1440-2880%minutes} for best results (1-72 hours acceptable). Chilling is especially important here — flax eggs and Earth Balance both encourage spread, and a long rest helps hydrate the flax and firm everything up.

Preheat oven: 30 minutes before dough finishes chilling, preheat oven to 350°F (175°C).

Bake: Bake for ~{11-13%minutes}, until edges are set and centers look slightly underdone. Vegan cookies often need an extra minute or so versus the original.

Cool: Rest on pan for ~{5%minutes}, then transfer to a wire cooling rack. They'll firm up significantly as they cool — flax-bound cookies can seem very soft straight from the oven.

> Flax eggs: 14g flaxseed meal + 90ml warm water replaces the whole egg + 2 yolks. Hydrate for a full 10 min — it should be visibly gloppy/gel-like before going in.

> Spread control: You're now stacking two spread-promoters (Earth Balance + flax). The 24-48 hr chill is no longer optional if you want round cookies. For thicker/taller cookies, freeze dough balls 30-60 min after refrigerating and bake from frozen, adding 1-2 minutes.

> Texture: Expect a slightly chewier, denser cookie than the egg version — flax binds well but doesn't aerate the way eggs do. The bread flour + cornstarch combo helps offset this.

> Doneness cue: Centers will look quite wet at the pull point. Trust the edges and the 5-min pan rest.

> If you want a cleaner flavor, you can use golden flax meal instead of regular brown — slightly less nutty.